{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"HIDConnectionEvent()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent/HIDConnectionEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebHID_API\">WebHID API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent\"><code>HIDConnectionEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><em><code>HIDConnectionEvent()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent/device\"><code>device</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for WebHID API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HID\"><code>HID</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDDevice\"><code>HIDDevice</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDInputReportEvent\"><code>HIDInputReportEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/hid\"><code>Navigator.hid</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div><div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect2\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>HIDConnectionEvent()</code></strong> constructor creates a new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent\"><code>HIDConnectionEvent</code></a> object. Typically this constructor is not used as events are created when an input report is received.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">new HIDConnectionEvent(type, options)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"type\"><code>type</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      A string with the name of the event.\n      It is case-sensitive and browsers set it to <code>connect</code> or <code>disconnect</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"options\"><code>options</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An object that, <em>in addition of the properties defined in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event/Event\" title=\"Event()\"><code>Event()</code></a></em>, can have the following properties:</p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"device\"><code>device</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDDevice\"><code>HIDDevice</code></a> instance representing the device sending the input report.</p>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent\"><code>HIDConnectionEvent</code></a> object.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/webhid/#dom-hidconnectionevent-constructor","title":"WebHID API"}],"query":"api.HIDConnectionEvent.HIDConnectionEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.HIDConnectionEvent.HIDConnectionEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent/HIDConnectionEvent/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The HIDConnectionEvent() constructor creates a new HIDConnectionEvent object. Typically this constructor is not used as events are created when an input report is received.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:48:35.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/hidconnectionevent/hidconnectionevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/hidconnectionevent/hidconnectionevent/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/8573240024adc1eef906b4b2df35567144fd733e","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent","title":"HIDConnectionEvent"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HIDConnectionEvent/HIDConnectionEvent","title":"HIDConnectionEvent()"}],"pageTitle":"HIDConnectionEvent() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}